BDO Leasing, First Philippine, Lopez: Philippine Stocks Preview

-- B y   I a n   C .   S a y s o n
-- 
2011-05-31T00:33:27Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-31/bdo-leasing-first-philippine-lopez-philippine-stocks-preview.html
Shares of the following companies may
have unusual moves in Philippine trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses, and prices are as of the previous close, unless
stated otherwise.  The Philippine Stock Exchange Index rose 0.5 percent to
4,295.24.  BDO Leasing & Finance Inc. (BLFI)  : The unit of the
largest Philippine bank by assets will broaden its loan
portfolio and aim for a “double digit” increase in profit this
year, a stock exchange filing showed. The stock fell 2.4 percent
to 1.61 pesos on May 27.  Banco de Oro Unibank Inc. (BDO)  ,
parent company of BDO Leasing, gained 2.6 percent to 57.80
pesos.  First Philippine Holdings Corp. (FPH)  : The company is
“evaluating” options to refinance its debts to “take
advantage of a favorable  debt market ,” Chief Finance Officer
Francis Giles Puno said. The company may use its cash to buy
back shares and reduce debt, he also said. The stock was
unchanged at 63 pesos. Lopez Holdings Corp. (LPZ PM), owner of
First Philippine, was unchanged at 6.36 pesos.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ian C. Sayson in Manila at 
 isayson@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
